      • add

        public boolean add(int index,
                   E data)
        Description copied from interface: LinkedList
        Adds given piece of data to the linked list at the given index. All items that were originally at the index or after the index should be shifted down by one. If the index specified is not valid, returns false. Otherwise, returns true. If the index specified is 0 or if it is one larger than the maximum current index (ie if index is equal to the size of the linked list), then this method should execute in O(1) (constant) time. This means that you should not iterate over the entire list to add the element, as it is unnecessary to do so.
        Specified by:
        add in interface LinkedList<E>
        Parameters:
        index - the index at which to add the item
        data - the item to be added to te linked list
        Returns:
        true if the data could be added at the given index
